      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a pristine 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2), a collector-grade widebody example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine with VarioCam Plus. This vehicle has undergone a proactive LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and features a documented clean borescope report. Power is managed via a G96 6-speed manual transaxle and a viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system. The chassis maintains factory-spec rigidity with refreshed bushings and Bilstein dampers, ensuring surgical turn-in and zero lateral play. Finished in Arctic Silver with consistent paint meter readings, the exterior is complemented by 18-inch 'Turbo Twist' alloys wrapped in new Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber. A mechanically flawless specimen with a clean DME report and a fully overhauled cooling system.",
